          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Humanitarian Firefighter Relief Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Tariff Act of 1930 and the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to grant duty-free treatment of donated fire-fighting and rescue and relief equipment and supplies imported by or on behalf of a qualified tax-exempt nonprofit charitable organization for purposes of the inspection and subsequent donation and export of those items to countries and organizations in need.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-09-08T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
